# ─── GitHub OAuth ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Create a GitHub OAuth App at: https://github.com/settings/developers
# Homepage URL:       https://your-app.vercel.app
# Callback URL:       https://your-app.vercel.app/api/auth
#
# Then set these in Vercel project settings → Environment Variables:
#   GITHUB_CLIENT_ID     (server-side, used in api/auth.js)
#   GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET (server-side, used in api/auth.js)
#   APP_ORIGIN           (server-side, e.g. https://your-app.vercel.app)
#
# And this in your local .env (prefix VITE_ so Vite exposes it to the browser):
VITE_GITHUB_CLIENT_ID=your_github_oauth_app_client_id

# ─── 1.0 External Smoke Checks ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# These are CLI-only variables used by `bun run check:external`.
# Do not prefix them with VITE_; they should not be exposed to the browser.
# Keep real values in your local shell or ignored `.env`, never commit them.
#
# AI smoke:
#   IFACE_AI_API_KEY      Required for `bun run check:external -- --ai`
#   IFACE_AI_BASE_URL     Optional; defaults to the app's default AI Base URL
#   IFACE_AI_MODEL        Optional; defaults to the app's default AI model
#   IFACE_AI_TIMEOUT_MS   Optional; defaults to 60000
#
# Gist smoke:
#   IFACE_GIST_TOKEN      Required for `bun run check:external -- --gist`
#                         Can also use GITHUB_TOKEN.
#
# IFACE_AI_API_KEY=your_ai_api_key
# IFACE_AI_BASE_URL=https://api.example.com/v1
# IFACE_AI_MODEL=your-model-id
# IFACE_AI_TIMEOUT_MS=60000
# IFACE_GIST_TOKEN=your_gist_token
